ou see an open door, there is no challenge there and therefore there is no joy! A door must be closed so that we can obtain the joy of trying to open it!', 3701, 0), (386279, 'Most intellectual training focuses on analytical skills. Whether in literary criticism or scientific investigation, the academic mind is best at taking things apart. The complementary arts of integration are far less well developed. This problem is at the core of human ecology. As with any interdisciplinary pursuit, it is the bridging across disparate ways of knowing that is the constant challenge.', 26085, 0), (386280, 'Looking away is submissive. Looking [..] in the eye is a challenge.', 73, 0), (386281, 'Challenges and Changes are part of Life, accept them and move on.', 24896, 0), (386282, 'The more challenging the obstacles in life, the greater the satisfaction in overcoming them.', 11078, 0), (386283, 'The challenge is what makes the success worthwhile.', 21804, 0), (386284, 'Most of these students are so conditioned to success that they become afraid to take risks. They have been taught from a young age by zealous parents, schools, and institutional authorities what constitutes failure and success. They are socialized to obey. They obsess over grades and seek to please professors, even if what professors teach is fatuous. The point is to get ahead, and getting ahead means deference to authority. Challenging authority is never a career advancer.', 3197, 0), (386285, 'Okay", I breathed. "Then what will it take?" I was completely out of my element. Begging a girl to go on a date with me. This was fucked up.""Miss it."I stared into her cold, blue eyes and knew I''d just met the kind of girl books are written about.', 602, 0), (386286, 'Change is like the skin peeling off of a snake. It is slow. It is sticky. And sometimes you have to rub against a hard place to pull yourself through it. But in the end, you realize that it was worth it all to get the the new place and new person you have become.', 26454, 0), (386287, 'Challenge conventional wisdom. There is almost always a better way.', 11230, 0), (386288, 'Every challenge in your life works out in the long run. If you can adopt this mindset, you’ll face your challenges with the knowledge and courage that it all works out in the end. You’ll no longer fear them and you’ll look forward to the lessons to be learned from every experience...', 9208, 0), (386289, 'The arbiter of a demanding wargame rendered the word "mismatch" as "challenge" in his language.', 30238, 0), (386290, '...I felt it would push me out of my comfort zone and develop my skills. And that''s what it''s all about - do something new and learn something from it.', 61125, 0), (386291, '...no way through it but through it," I tell myself.', 150, 0), (386292, 'Your best teacher is the person offering you your greatest challenge.', 55470, 0), (386293, 'His last thought flashed like a mantra over and over again.Let the challenge begin.', 41005, 0), (386294, 'People rise to the occasion without hesitation when they feel inspired and challenged.', 3540, 0), (386295, 'From within the mind we look out and envision, contemplating and interpreting each new challenge and the action we will take.', 3540, 0), (386296, 'The future of fiction? he said. Maybe, she said. Will it have room for, you know, love & stuff? he said. Always, she said. OK then, he said.', 258, 0), (386297, 'We all know what needs to be done - it''s the doing it that is the challenge!', 61126, 0), (386298, 'In the future, we should anticipate seeing more hybrid wars where conventional warfare, irregular warfare, asymmetric warfare, and information warfare all blend together, creating a very complex and challenging situation to the combatants; therefore it will require military forces to posses hybrid capabilities, which might help deal with hybrid threats.', 49962, 0), (386299, 'Don’t challenge the world before becoming a big fire', 61127, 0), (386300, 'The desire to do something be